Class PushPullED

All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, Protocol, EDProtocol, AggregationProtocol
public class PushPullED
extends Object
implements AggregationProtocol, EDProtocol

An event-driven implementation of the Push-Pull protocol.

In each step, each node selects a random neighbor and sets the estimate of the neighbor and of itself to the mean of their current estimates.

This protocol expects the following additional parameters in the configuration file:

step - the time between timer messages signalling the start of the next step

Author:
Dario Seidl
